64kmh Why is Death Valley so hot? Sacramento San Francisco • 1 shallow pond Rain creates a in the playa which freezes over during cold winter nights Nevada Its geographic­al features – a lower-than-sea-level basin and surroundin­g mountains Las Vegas California – create a ‘pocket’ which traps and circulates superheate­d air, making it the driest and hottest spot in North America 2 • On sunny days, the ice melts and breaks up to form Los Angeles large rafts of thin ice floats Arizona • Area enlarged 3 4 Light wind Stones are pushed forward pushes the ice floats against the stones • Hotly contested records 1st Death Valley, California • It is one of five pupfish species found in the park and is critically endangered
