Its final holdout is a water-filled limestone cavern in the Nevadan desert dating to the last Ice Age July 10, 1913 5 Stones leave trail imprints in the 2nd soft mud Kebili, Tunisia • July 7, 1931 S’porean runner who conquered Death Valley • 3rd & 4th Mitribah, Kuwait Turbat, Pakistan • July 21, 2016 May 28, 2017 60-year-old Lim Nghee Huat took the 58th spot out of 96 competitor­s in an ultramarat­hon at Death Valley in July 2013. He completed the 217km footrace in 42 hours and 34 minutes and helped raise $130,000 for a charity. The World Meteorolog­ical Organisati­on will verify the temperatur­e of 54.4 deg C in Death Valley. This could take months or even years.
The high temperatur­e comes amid an extensive heatwave on the west coast of the US that is due to a persistent heat dome which occurs when the atmosphere traps hot ocean air like a lid. Climate change is fuelling the frequency, duration and intensity of such high-pressure domes. • Temperatur­e-measuring equipment at Furnace Creek Sources: NATIONAL PARK SERVICE (NPS), NATIONAL GEOGRAPHIC, NATIONAL OCEANIC AND ATMOSPHERI­C ADMINISTRA­TION (NOAA) PHOTOS: NPS, NOAA, ISTOCK, ST FILE STRAITS TIMES GRAPHICS: LIM YONG PRINTED AND DISTRIBUTE­D BY PRESSREADE­R PressReade­r.com +1 604 278 4604 ORIGINAL COPY . ORIGINAL COPY . ORIGINAL COPY . ORIGINAL COPY . ORIGINAL COPY . ORIGINAL COPY COPYRIGHT AND PROTECTED BY APPLICABLE LAW 400 • • lowest point 56.7°C 55°C >970 US The beautiful landscape of Death Valley's Golden Canyon and Panamint Range. • 54°C
